   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>LIFE-STUDY OF FIRST AND SECOND SAMUEL MESSAGE THIRTY-EIGHT THE HISTORY CONCERNING DAVID 16 CROWNED BY THE PEOPLE TO BE THE KING</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>FOR THE KINGDOM OF GOD ON THE EARTH</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>2 SAMUEL 2 24 10 THE LAST STAGE OF DAVID'S KINGSHIP</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>2 SAMUEL 21 24 Scripture Reading: 2 Sam 21 24</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>In this message we will consider the last stage of David's kingship.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>I. DAVID'S TAKING CARE OF THE FAMINE</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>FOR THE PEOPLE</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>In 21:1-14 David took care of the famine for the people.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>A. Inquiring of Jehovah</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>This famine lasted three years, and David inquired of Jehovah concerning it v. 1a .</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>B. Finding Out the Reason for the Famine</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>David found out that the reason for the famine was Saul's breaking of the oath made by Israel with the Gibeonites.</S>
   <S PAR='13' RSNT='1' SNO='13'>The famine was "because of Saul and because of his house of bloodshed, for he put those Gibeonites to death" v. 1b . David called for the Gibeonites and spoke to them v. 2a .</S>
   <S PAR='14' RSNT='1' SNO='14'>C. The Settlement of the Breaking of the Oath</S>
   <S PAR='15' RSNT='1' SNO='15'>For the settlement of the breaking of the oath, the Gibeonites required seven descendants of Saul to be executed vv.</S>
   <S PAR='16' RSNT='1' SNO='16'>2b-14a .</S>
   <S PAR='17' RSNT='1' SNO='17'>David commanded the people to fulfill the requirement of the Gibeonites, and God responded to the people's entreaty for the land v. 14b .</S>
   </TEXT>
